==Old English==
===Etymology===
Germanic ''*murþran'', from Indo-European ''*mer-'' ‘die’.

''Germanic cognates:'' Gothic [[𐌼𐌰𐌿𐍂𐌸𐍂]].

''Indo-European cognates:'' Greek [[ἔμορτεν]], Latin [[mors]], Old Church Slavonic [[мрѣти]] (Russian [[мереть]]), Lithuanian [[mirti]], Old Irish [[marb]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /'moɹðoɹ/

===Noun===
'''morþor''' ''n'' or ''m''
# [[murder]]
# a great [[sin]] or [[crime]]

===Related words===
*[[morþ]]

